Muriel LOOFBURROW v. Eldon MILLER. No. 3865. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Feb. 28, 1949. Claude L. Rice, of Kansas City, Kan., for appellant. N. E. Snyder, James L. Hogin, and Blake A Williamson, all of Kansas City, Kan., for appellee.

Before PPIILLIPS, Chief Judge, and HUXMAN andMURRAH, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed, on motion of ap-pellee, for failure to prosecute.
